<HEAD>Small Plane Lands on Freeway Overpass</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small plane made an emergency landing on a
freeway overpass and struck a car, but no serious injuries or major
damage was reported, officials said.
   The single-engine Cessna carrying a man and woman landed Sunday
afternoon on the eastbound lane of Sunland Boulevard overpass of
the Golden State Freeway, said Jim Wells, a city Fire Department
spokesman.
   The man suffered a head cut and injuries to the back and neck,
said Wells. The woman suffered a minor back injury.
   They were taken to Pacifica of the Valley Hospital, he said.
   The car that was struck sustained only minor damage, Wells said.
The driver was not injured.
   The pilot reported engine trouble before landing the plane about
a half-mile north of Burbank Airport, said a Federal Aviation
Administration official who declined to give his name.
