and Womens' Hospital, where they had attended a birthing class.
   Stuart, 29, was listed in stable condition Monday in intensive
care after having surgery Saturday at Boston City Hospital, but
hospital officials would not give a reason for the surgery.
   The infant was delivered by Caesarean section and clung to life
for more than two weeks before succumbing to a respiratory ailment
Thursday. The medical examiner ruled his death a homicide.
   In the Brookline courtroom, Crowley granted a motion by attorney
Joel Goodman to let Bennett sit concealed behind the witness stand.
   Goodman said the repeated publication of Bennett's picture could
bias witnesses or potential jurors.
   Bennett's presence in the Charlestown court had been waived
because of the publicity surrounding his arrest.
