<HEAD>Prisoners Take 40 Hostages in Southern Brazil</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eight inmates wielding iron clubs
and revolvers seized 40 hostages at a prison cafeteria in southern
Brazil, a state official said Monday.
   Negotiations were being conducted with the prisoners and 300
heavily armed policeman had cordoned off the building, said Rubens
Buelo, a justice official in Curitiba, capital of Parana state, 525
miles southwest of Rio.
   Buelo said the hostages, all employees of the Central Prison of
Parana, include the director, deputy director and several staff
psychologists. He said the 40 were taken hostage in the cafeteria
during the lunch hour.
   The prisoners were demanding more weapons and an armored car for
a getaway, Buelo said.
   ``We're sure negotiations will be successful,'' Buelo said.
``We're doing our best to keep everyone calm and confort the
families of the hostages.''
