with the talks expected to lay the groundwork for increased trade
between the two countries, U.S. officials say.
   Commerce Secretary Robert Mosbacher will head the U.S.
delegation to the discussions, which will take place Wednesday and
Thursday at the Commerce Department. His Soviet counterpart will be
Konstantin F. Katushev, Soviet minister of foreign economic
relations.
</TEXT>
