<FIRST>r f BC-Meredith-GolfMagazine     11-13 0184</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Meredith-Golf Magazine,0192</SECOND>
<HEAD>Meredith Corp. Adds Golf For Women Magazine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Meredith Corp., the publisher of Better
Homes and Gardens and Ladies' Home Journal, announced Monday it has
purchased Golf For Women magazine from Brumitt Publishing of
Oxford, Miss.
   Terms were not disclosed.
   Of Meredith's 12 other subscription magazines, the only other
sports-related publication is Sail.
   ``The game of golf is exploding in popularity, but women golfers
have been among the most neglected sports people in the nation,''
said Jim Autry, president of the magazine group of the publishing,
broadcasting and real estate company. ``As nearly half of all
beginning golfers are women, we're excited by the opportunities
this market represents.''
   Meredith said the magazine's editorial headquarters would remain
in Mississippi under the direction of founders Debra and Woody
Brumitt.
   Effective with the April 1990 issue, which goes on sale in
mid-February, Golf For Women will have a circulation of 200,000,
including newsstand and subscription sales, Meredith said.
   The magazine comes out six times a year with a cover price of
$2.50 and an annual subscription rate of $14.97.
</TEXT>
